.TH PERSIST-ENABLED 1 "June 2026" "mx-remaster" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
persist-enabled \- report whether root persistence is enabled
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B persist-enabled
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B persist-enabled
is a tiny probe helper used by the live workflow to check whether the root
persistence feature is enabled.
If the expected persistence marker exists, it prints
.B Persist Root Enabled
and exits successfully.
Otherwise it exits silently with a non-zero status.

The script is primarily intended for menu logic, startup hooks, and other small
checks where only the presence of root persistence matters.
.SH OPTIONS
.B persist-enabled
accepts no options.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/live/config/persist-root
Configuration marker checked first.
.TP
.I /live/config/persist-root
Fallback live configuration marker.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR persist-config (1),
.BR persist-save (1)
.SH AUTHOR
mx-remaster maintainers
